        text: `The convergence of geopolitical tensions, the US-China trade war, strategic competition in artificial intelligence (AI), and political realignments are reshaping the global economy, supply chains and technological deployment. Singapore, as a small, open economy, is particularly sensitive to these shifts. Ms Tin Pei Ling (MacPherson) The US-China trade war resulted in increased tariffs on approximately $1.4 trillion in imports. The tariffs have disrupted global supply chains, leading to uncertainty and volatility in markets. The rivalry is so strong that the US and China are willing to risk hur`,
