        text: `Mr Chairman, since a long time pre-Independence, our geographical centrality has made trade the lifeblood of Singapore's economy. Our 15 bilateral and 12 regional Free Trade Agreements (FTAs) are key to our open economy driven by trade in goods and services. Mr Saktiandi Supaat (Bishan-Toa Payoh) But the world's multilateral trading system is coming under real pressure. During President Trump's first presidential term, the United States (US) withdrew from the Trans-Pacific Partnership. As Trump 2.0 starts this year, the US has already announced a host of tariffs on imports from China, Canada a`,
