        speaker: `Mr Teo Ser Luck (Pasir Ris-Punggol)`,
        text: `Our economic growth is getting more and more challenging. I think each year, as we forecast our economic growth, you will realise that we keep revising our forecast. From last year to this year, we are revising downwards on the forecast. It is challenging, no doubt, and, with COVID-19, it is getting more and more challenging to actually get a part of the pie because other cities and economies are also getting more competitive. Mr Teo Ser Luck (Pasir Ris-Punggol) We are focusing on quite a few verticals and I know that we rely less on manufacturing now, which, in the past, was about 25% contrib`,
